        <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Jonathan Perl</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=40656805\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/jon_perl\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"jonBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Founder and President, Technology</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Jon started FoundOPS because of the great deal of potential he sees for the future for technology. He \r\n\r\nbelieves that the next revolution \r\n                belongs to small business. “Everyday we see technology breaking down barriers and making more resources \r\n\r\navailable.” FoundOPS hopes to help \r\n                small businesses harness the incredible resources and opportunities that are now available to them.</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                At 21, Jonathan may be young, but he is no newcomer to the world of business software. During high school \r\n\r\nJonathan got his start working \r\n                as software consultant for the service industry. In college, he knew the potential that existed for a small \r\n\r\nbusiness software platform \r\n                and began working on a solution. The prototypes he developed have become the precursor to FoundOPS.</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                When asked what he likes to do in his free time, Jonathan responds “Free time?” Despite his borderline \r\n\r\nobsessive commitment to FoundOPS, \r\n                Jonathan still manages to sneak out of the office for the occasional bike ride or run. He’ll also read \r\n\r\nanything he can get his hands if \r\n                he thinks it will give him a bit of knowledge. One day Jonathan hopes to have some time to travel the world \r\n\r\nand just meet people but for \r\n                now he is happy right where he is.</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"orenBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"orenImg\" src=\"../Content/Oren.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"Oren Shatken\" />\r\n        <div id=\"orenDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Oren Shatken</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72288581\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a \r\n\r\nhref=\"http://twitter.com/#!/OrenShatken\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"orenBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Cofounder and President, Product</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                The son of an artist and an architect, Oren has always been torn between the worlds of form and function. \r\n\r\nAt Purdue, Oren studied \r\n                an eclectic mix of Political Science, Art and Design, Entrepreneurship, Viticulture, and Jewish Studies. \r\n\r\nEventually he was approached \r\n                by Jonathan with an interesting application of both form and function. “From what I’ve seen, business \r\n\r\nenterprise software suffers from \r\n                an impressive lack of both. These issues are the result of years of decision-makers at large corporations \r\n\r\nwith the luxury of not having \r\n                to use the software they were purchasing.”</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Now Oren believes user interface has emerged as one of the most significant considerations for the future. \r\n\r\n“Technology has progressed \r\n                to such an advanced stage that the bottleneck has become the connection between technology and the users. \r\n\r\nComputers now wait for us \r\n                more than we wait for them.” By emphasizing simple and clean design practice, Oren hopes to create an \r\n\r\ninterface that users will find \r\n                intuitive and even addicting to use. “One day FoundOPS will be done when it does everything our users want \r\n\r\nand nothing else.”</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Beyond software, Oren loves spending time with his family and friends out on Shelter Island. An avid \r\n\r\nsailor, he claims his first crib \r\n                was the v-berth (the triangle shaped bed located in the very front of a boat) on his father’s Cape Dory \r\n\r\nsailboat. When the snow falls \r\n                outside the FoundOPS office, Oren dreams about skiing, but he’s concerned his techniques has suffered since \r\n\r\nhe moved out to Indiana.</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"zachBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"zachImg\" src=\"../Content/Zach.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"Zach Bright\" />\r\n        <div id=\"zachDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Zach Bright</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72290770\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/zbbright\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"zachBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Senior Software Engineer</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                A die-hard Cubs fan, Zach hails from the suburbs of Chicago. At Purdue, Zach was a distinguished student of \r\n\r\nComputer Engineering, \r\n                the president of his fraternity, all while working as a teaching assistant. Working with an entire \r\n\r\nfraternity of men or a class \r\n                full of students taught Zach a great deal of patience. While Jon and Oren’s passion can create a great deal \r\n\r\nof excitement, we can \r\n                always rely on Zach’s calming disposition to maintain order at FoundOPS.</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Zach loves getting outside on a nice day and playing a few holes of golf. He’ll be happy where ever he is \r\n\r\nin the world as long \r\n                he can tune in to watch the Cubs play.\r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"andrewBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"andrewImg\" src=\"../Content/Andrew.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"Andrew Pohl\" />\r\n        <div id=\"andrewDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Andrew Pohl</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=70782535\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/apohl1111\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"andrewBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Silverlight Developer and Designer</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Andrew grew up in rural Indiana on a farm which might have something to do with his strong work ethic. “I \r\n\r\nleave work not when \r\n                I’m tired, but when I’m done.” After earning his degree from Purdue in Computer Graphics Technology, Andrew \r\n\r\njoined the FoundOPS \r\n                team as a Silverlight developer and has been invaluable for creating the look and feel of the site. </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                When he’s not working on the project, Andrew enjoys spending time outdoors and playing Ultimate Frisbee. \r\n\r\nOccasionally he can be \r\n                found kicking back and watching an action movie or two. His goals are modest but quickly becoming \r\n\r\nfulfilled; to be successful at something he enjoys.</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"ankitBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"ankitImg\" src=\"../Content/BlankPhoto.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"Ankit Buti\" />\r\n        <div id=\"ankitDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Ankit Buti</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=62466824\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/FoundOps\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"ankitBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Android Developer</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Perhaps it’s appropriate that FoundOPS mobile platform is developed by an engineer from who has traveled to \r\n\r\nus from the other side \r\n                of the globe. Ankit grew up in New Delhi before coming to the states to attend college. He has always had a \r\n\r\npassion for mobile phone \r\n                development and is especially excited about the Android platform. \r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"johnBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"johnImg\" src=\"../Content/BlankPhoto.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"John Mahoney\" />\r\n        <div id=\"johnDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    John Mahoney</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=42714775\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/FoundOps\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"johnBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Software Engineer</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                John was originally from Virginia before moving out to California to study aerospace engineering. Before \r\n\r\njoining the FoundOPS team, \r\n                John worked in IT for a number of years. Nowadays, John is known as the algorithms guys and has been \r\n\r\nresponsible for developing much \r\n                of the logic that makes FoundOPS dispatching so efficient.</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                In his spare time, John can be found working with his hands on various construction projects. He also \r\n\r\nenjoys producing music. One day \r\n                John hopes to turn his talents towards space exploration.\r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n        <ul id=\"footerList\">\r\n            <li>Connect&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n            <li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/FoundOPS/202962066405323\">\r\n                <img class=\"footerIcon\" style=\"padding-right: 5px\" src=\"<%= Url.Content(\"../Content/facebook.png\")%>\"\r\n                    border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></li>\r\n            <li><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/company/foundops\">\r\n                <img class=\"footerIcon\" src=\"<%= Url.Content(\"../Content/linkedin.png\")%>\" alt=\"\"\r\n                    border=\"0\" /></a></li>\r\n            <li><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/FoundOPS\">\r\n                <img class=\"footerIcon\" src=\"<%= Url.Content(\"../Content/twitter.png\")%>\" border=\"0\"\r\n                    alt=\"\" /></a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n        <table id=\"bottomTable\" class=\"tabs\">\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td rowspan=\"5\" valign=\"middle\">\r\n                    <a href=\"<%Response.Write(Global.IsDebugMode ? \"http://localhost:31820\" : \"http://www.foundops.com\");\r\n\r\n%>\">\r\n                        <img id=\"navLogo\" src=\"<%= Url.Content(\"../Content/navLogo.png\") %>\" alt=\"\" />\r\n                    </a>\r\n                </td>\r\n                <td class=\"bigFooterText\"><%: Html.ActionLink(\"FoundOPS\", \"Product\", \"Home\")%>\r\n                </td>\r\n                <td class=\"bigFooterText\"><%: Html.ActionLink(\"About Us\", \"Company\", \"Home\")%>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Beta Program\", \"Product\", \"Home\")%> </td>\r\n                <td><%: Html.ActionLink(\"The Team\", \"Team\", \"Home\")%></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td> <%: Html.ActionLink(\"Features\", \"Product\", \"Home\")%> </td>\r\n                <td><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Our Values\", \"Company\", \"Home\")%></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n                <td><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Contact Us\", \"ContactUs\", \"Home\")%></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n                <td><a href=\"http://localhost:15880/\">Blog</a></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n        <div>\r\n            &copy;2011&nbsp;FOUNDOPS&nbsp;LLC</div>\r\n        <br />\r\n    </div>','The Team','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-11','','','2011-09-15 13:13:10','2011-09-15 17:13:10','',21,'http://localhost:15880/2011/09/15/21-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(36,1,'2011-09-15 13:13:18','2011-09-15 17:13:18','<style type=\"text\'css\">\r\n\r\n.tabs li\r\n{\r\n    position:relative;\r\n    top:-12px;\r\n    left:-40px;\r\n    width:170px;\r\n    font-size:14px;\r\n    font-weight:bold;\r\n    list-style:none;\r\n    border-top: 1px solid White;\r\n    margin-bottom:5px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.tabs li a\r\n{\r\n    position:relative;\r\n    left:20px;\r\n}\r\n\r\nul.tabs li a:hover, ul.tabs li a:active, ul.tabs li a:focus\r\n{\r\n    color:#ccc;\r\n}\r\n\r\nul.tabs a:link, ul.tabs a:visited\r\n{\r\n    color:#fff;\r\n}\r\n\r\n ul.tabs.homeTab\r\n {\r\n     border-top:none;\r\n }\r\n\r\n.subNav\r\n{\r\n    margin-bottom:-5px;\r\n    background-color:#555;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.subNav li\r\n{\r\n    position:relative;\r\n    top:0px;\r\n    left:-20px;\r\n    height:25px;\r\n    font-size:14px;\r\n    font-weight:normal;\r\n    list-style:none;\r\n    border-top: none;\r\n    margin-bottom:0px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#ourTeam\r\n{\r\n    position:relative;\r\n    top:-35px;\r\n    left:230px;\r\n    width:750px;\r\n    margin-bottom:100px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n#navBoxTeam\r\n{\r\n    position:relative;\r\n    top:-95px;\r\n    left:-220px;\r\n    height:150px;/*195 with subnav*/\r\n    width:170px;\r\n    background-color: #333335;\r\n    border:2px outset #666;\r\n    margin-bottom:-250px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.greyText\r\n{\r\n    color:#555;\r\n    margin-top:-35px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.bigText\r\n{\r\n    font-size:18px;\r\n    font-weight:bold;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.links\r\n{\r\n    position:absolute;\r\n    top:30px;\r\n    margin-left:580px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#jonImg, #orenImg, #zachImg, #andrewImg, #ankitImg, #johnImg\r\n{\r\n    position:relative;\r\n    top:243px;\r\n    left:5px;\r\n    border: 4px solid #fff;\r\n    border-radius:15px;\r\n    margin-top:-270px;\r\n    width:185px;\r\n    height:185px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#jonImg\r\n{\r\n    top:-17px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#jonBg, #orenBg, #zachBg, #andrewBg, #ankitBg, #johnBg\r\n{\r\n    position:relative;\r\n    top:260px;\r\n    left:0px;\r\n    width:203px;\r\n    height:203px;\r\n    border-radius:15px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#jonBg\r\n{\r\n    top:0px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#jonBar, #jonBg\r\n{\r\n    background-color:#659A41;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#orenBg, #orenBar\r\n{\r\n    background-color:#D9591E;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#zachBg, #zachBar\r\n{\r\n    background-color:#991A36;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#andrewBg, #andrewBar\r\n{\r\n    background-color:#488FCD;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#ankitBg, #ankitBar\r\n{\r\n    background-color:#E40000;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#johnBg, #johnBar\r\n{\r\n    background-color:#CE00CE;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#jonBar, #orenBar, #zachBar, #andrewBar, #ankitBar, #johnBar\r\n{\r\n    position:relative;\r\n    top:10px;\r\n    left:-5px;\r\n    width:635px;\r\n    height:4px;\r\n    border-radius:2px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#jonDesc, #orenDesc, #zachDesc, #andrewDesc, #ankitDesc, #johnDesc\r\n{\r\n    position:relative;\r\n    margin-top:-35px;\r\n    top:60px;\r\n    left:260px;\r\n    width:630px;\r\n    margin-bottom:-200px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#jonDesc\r\n{\r\n    margin-top:-295px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#andrewDesc\r\n{\r\n    margin-bottom:-180px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#ankitDesc\r\n{\r\n    margin-bottom:-100px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#johnDesc\r\n{\r\n    margin-bottom:-40px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n<style/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id=\"ourTeam\">\r\n        <div id=\"navBoxTeam\">\r\n            <ul class=\"tabs\">\r\n                <li style=\"border-top:none\"><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Home\", \"Index\", \"Home\")%></li>\r\n                <li><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Our Solution\", \"Product\", \"Home\")%></li>\r\n                <li><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Our Company\", \"Company\", \"Home\")%></li>\r\n                <li><%: Html.ActionLink(\"The Team\", \"Team\", \"Home\")%>\r\n                    <%--<ul class=\"subNav\">\r\n                        <li><a href=\"#\">Members</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"#\">Advisors</a></li>\r\n                    </ul>--%>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"http://localhost:15880/\">Blog</a></li>\r\n                <li><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Contact Us\", \"ContactUs\", \"Home\")%></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"jonBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"jonImg\" src=\"../Content/Jon.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"Jonathan Perl\" />\r\n        <div id=\"jonDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Jonathan Perl</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=40656805\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/jon_perl\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"jonBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Founder and President, Technology</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Jon started FoundOPS because of the great deal of potential he sees for the future for technology. He \r\n\r\nbelieves that the next revolution \r\n                belongs to small business. “Everyday we see technology breaking down barriers and making more resources \r\n\r\navailable.” FoundOPS hopes to help \r\n                small businesses harness the incredible resources and opportunities that are now available to them.</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                At 21, Jonathan may be young, but he is no newcomer to the world of business software. During high school \r\n\r\nJonathan got his start working \r\n                as software consultant for the service industry. In college, he knew the potential that existed for a small \r\n\r\nbusiness software platform \r\n                and began working on a solution. The prototypes he developed have become the precursor to FoundOPS.</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                When asked what he likes to do in his free time, Jonathan responds “Free time?” Despite his borderline \r\n\r\nobsessive commitment to FoundOPS, \r\n                Jonathan still manages to sneak out of the office for the occasional bike ride or run. He’ll also read \r\n\r\nanything he can get his hands if \r\n                he thinks it will give him a bit of knowledge. One day Jonathan hopes to have some time to travel the world \r\n\r\nand just meet people but for \r\n                now he is happy right where he is.</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"orenBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"orenImg\" src=\"../Content/Oren.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"Oren Shatken\" />\r\n        <div id=\"orenDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Oren Shatken</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72288581\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a \r\n\r\nhref=\"http://twitter.com/#!/OrenShatken\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"orenBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Cofounder and President, Product</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                The son of an artist and an architect, Oren has always been torn between the worlds of form and function. \r\n\r\nAt Purdue, Oren studied \r\n                an eclectic mix of Political Science, Art and Design, Entrepreneurship, Viticulture, and Jewish Studies. \r\n\r\nEventually he was approached \r\n                by Jonathan with an interesting application of both form and function. “From what I’ve seen, business \r\n\r\nenterprise software suffers from \r\n                an impressive lack of both. These issues are the result of years of decision-makers at large corporations \r\n\r\nwith the luxury of not having \r\n                to use the software they were purchasing.”</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Now Oren believes user interface has emerged as one of the most significant considerations for the future. \r\n\r\n“Technology has progressed \r\n                to such an advanced stage that the bottleneck has become the connection between technology and the users. \r\n\r\nComputers now wait for us \r\n                more than we wait for them.” By emphasizing simple and clean design practice, Oren hopes to create an \r\n\r\ninterface that users will find \r\n                intuitive and even addicting to use. “One day FoundOPS will be done when it does everything our users want \r\n\r\nand nothing else.”</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Beyond software, Oren loves spending time with his family and friends out on Shelter Island. An avid \r\n\r\nsailor, he claims his first crib \r\n                was the v-berth (the triangle shaped bed located in the very front of a boat) on his father’s Cape Dory \r\n\r\nsailboat. When the snow falls \r\n                outside the FoundOPS office, Oren dreams about skiing, but he’s concerned his techniques has suffered since \r\n\r\nhe moved out to Indiana.</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"zachBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"zachImg\" src=\"../Content/Zach.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"Zach Bright\" />\r\n        <div id=\"zachDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Zach Bright</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72290770\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/zbbright\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"zachBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Senior Software Engineer</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                A die-hard Cubs fan, Zach hails from the suburbs of Chicago. At Purdue, Zach was a distinguished student of \r\n\r\nComputer Engineering, \r\n                the president of his fraternity, all while working as a teaching assistant. Working with an entire \r\n\r\nfraternity of men or a class \r\n                full of students taught Zach a great deal of patience. While Jon and Oren’s passion can create a great deal \r\n\r\nof excitement, we can \r\n                always rely on Zach’s calming disposition to maintain order at FoundOPS.</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Zach loves getting outside on a nice day and playing a few holes of golf. He’ll be happy where ever he is \r\n\r\nin the world as long \r\n                he can tune in to watch the Cubs play.\r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"andrewBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"andrewImg\" src=\"../Content/Andrew.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"Andrew Pohl\" />\r\n        <div id=\"andrewDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Andrew Pohl</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=70782535\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/apohl1111\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"andrewBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Silverlight Developer and Designer</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Andrew grew up in rural Indiana on a farm which might have something to do with his strong work ethic. “I \r\n\r\nleave work not when \r\n                I’m tired, but when I’m done.” After earning his degree from Purdue in Computer Graphics Technology, Andrew \r\n\r\njoined the FoundOPS \r\n                team as a Silverlight developer and has been invaluable for creating the look and feel of the site. </p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                When he’s not working on the project, Andrew enjoys spending time outdoors and playing Ultimate Frisbee. \r\n\r\nOccasionally he can be \r\n                found kicking back and watching an action movie or two. His goals are modest but quickly becoming \r\n\r\nfulfilled; to be successful at something he enjoys.</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"ankitBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"ankitImg\" src=\"../Content/BlankPhoto.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"Ankit Buti\" />\r\n        <div id=\"ankitDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Ankit Buti</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=62466824\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/FoundOps\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"ankitBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Android Developer</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                Perhaps it’s appropriate that FoundOPS mobile platform is developed by an engineer from who has traveled to \r\n\r\nus from the other side \r\n                of the globe. Ankit grew up in New Delhi before coming to the states to attend college. He has always had a \r\n\r\npassion for mobile phone \r\n                development and is especially excited about the Android platform. \r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div id=\"johnBg\">\r\n        </div>\r\n        <img id=\"johnImg\" src=\"../Content/BlankPhoto.png\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\" alt=\"John Mahoney\" />\r\n        <div id=\"johnDesc\">\r\n            <div class=\"bigText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    John Mahoney</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"links\">\r\n                <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=42714775\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../Content/linkedin.png\" alt=\"\" border=\"0\" /></a> <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/FoundOps\">\r\n                        <img src=\"../Content/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\r\n            <div id=\"johnBar\">\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class=\"greyText\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Software Engineer</p>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <p>\r\n                John was originally from Virginia before moving out to California to study aerospace engineering. Before \r\n\r\njoining the FoundOPS team, \r\n                John worked in IT for a number of years. Nowadays, John is known as the algorithms guys and has been \r\n\r\nresponsible for developing much \r\n                of the logic that makes FoundOPS dispatching so efficient.</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n                In his spare time, John can be found working with his hands on various construction projects. He also \r\n\r\nenjoys producing music. One day \r\n                John hopes to turn his talents towards space exploration.\r\n            </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n        <ul id=\"footerList\">\r\n            <li>Connect&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n            <li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/FoundOPS/202962066405323\">\r\n                <img class=\"footerIcon\" style=\"padding-right: 5px\" src=\"<%= Url.Content(\"../Content/facebook.png\")%>\"\r\n                    border=\"0\" alt=\"\" /></a></li>\r\n            <li><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/company/foundops\">\r\n                <img class=\"footerIcon\" src=\"<%= Url.Content(\"../Content/linkedin.png\")%>\" alt=\"\"\r\n                    border=\"0\" /></a></li>\r\n            <li><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/FoundOPS\">\r\n                <img class=\"footerIcon\" src=\"<%= Url.Content(\"../Content/twitter.png\")%>\" border=\"0\"\r\n                    alt=\"\" /></a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n        <table id=\"bottomTable\" class=\"tabs\">\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td rowspan=\"5\" valign=\"middle\">\r\n                    <a href=\"<%Response.Write(Global.IsDebugMode ? \"http://localhost:31820\" : \"http://www.foundops.com\");\r\n\r\n%>\">\r\n                        <img id=\"navLogo\" src=\"<%= Url.Content(\"../Content/navLogo.png\") %>\" alt=\"\" />\r\n                    </a>\r\n                </td>\r\n                <td class=\"bigFooterText\"><%: Html.ActionLink(\"FoundOPS\", \"Product\", \"Home\")%>\r\n                </td>\r\n                <td class=\"bigFooterText\"><%: Html.ActionLink(\"About Us\", \"Company\", \"Home\")%>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Beta Program\", \"Product\", \"Home\")%> </td>\r\n                <td><%: Html.ActionLink(\"The Team\", \"Team\", \"Home\")%></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td> <%: Html.ActionLink(\"Features\", \"Product\", \"Home\")%> </td>\r\n                <td><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Our Values\", \"Company\", \"Home\")%></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n                <td><%: Html.ActionLink(\"Contact Us\", \"ContactUs\", \"Home\")%></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n                <td><a href=\"http://localhost:15880/\">Blog</a></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n        <div>\r\n            &copy;2011&nbsp;FOUNDOPS&nbsp;LLC</div>\r\n        <br />\r\n    </div>','The Team','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-12','','','2011-09-15 13:13:18','2011-09-15 17:13:18','',21,'http://localhost:15880/2011/09/15/21-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(37,1,'2011-09-23 12:26:59','2011-09-23 16:26:59','<div style=\"position: relative; top: -55px; left: 300px; background: none; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px;\">\n<div id=\"navBoxTeam\">\n            <ul class=\"tabs\">\n                <li style=\"border-top:none;\"><?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>\">Home</a></li>\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">FoundOPS</a>\n                    <%--<ul class=\"subNav\">\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">Beta</a></li>\n                        <li><?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>/Home/Product\">Features</a></li>\n                    </ul>--%>\n                </li>    \n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">About Us</a>\n                    <ul class=\"subNav\">\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">The Team</a></li>\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/values\">Our Values</a></li>\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/jobs\">Jobs</a></li>\n                        <li><?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>/Home/ContactUs\">Contact Us</a></li>\n                    </ul>\n                </li>\n                <li><a href=\"<%= Global.RootBlogUrl %>\">Blog</a></li>\n            </ul>\n        </div>\n<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The Team</h1>\n<div class=\"titleBar\"></div>\n<div class=\"titleText\">Lorem ipsum non habent claritatem insitam; est usus legentis in iis qui facit eorum claritatem. Investigationes demonstraverunt lectores legere me lius quod ii legunt saepius. Claritas est etiam processus dynamicus, qui sequitur mutationem consuetudium lectorum.</div>\n<div id=\"jonBg\"></div>\n<div id=\"jonImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\n<div id=\"jonDesc\">\n<div class=\"bigText\">\n\nJonathan Perl\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=40656805\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/jon_perl\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\n<div id=\"jonBar\"></div>\n<div class=\"greyText\">\n\nFounder and President, Technology\n\n</div>\nJon started FoundOPS because of the great deal of potential he sees for the future for technology. He believes that the next revolution belongs to small business. “Everyday we see technology breaking down barriers and making more resources available.” FoundOPS hopes to help small businesses harness the incredible resources and opportunities that are now available to them.\n\nAt 21, Jonathan may be young, but he is no newcomer to the world of business software. During high school Jonathan got his start working as software consultant for the service industry. In college, he knew the potential that existed for a small business software platform and began working on a solution. The prototypes he developed have become the precursor to FoundOPS.\n\nWhen asked what he likes to do in his free time, Jonathan responds “Free time?” Despite his borderline obsessive commitment to FoundOPS, Jonathan still manages to sneak out of the office for the occasional bike ride or run. He’ll also read anything he can get his hands if he thinks it will give him a bit of knowledge. One day Jonathan hopes to have some time to travel the world and just meet people but for now he is happy right where he is.\n\n</div>\n<div id=\"orenBg\"></div>\n<div id=\"orenImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\n<div id=\"orenDesc\">\n<div class=\"bigText\">\n\nOren Shatken\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72288581\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/OrenShatken\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\n<div id=\"orenBar\"></div>\n<div class=\"greyText\">\n\nCofounder and President, Product\n\n</div>\nThe son of an artist and an architect, Oren has always been torn between the worlds of form and function. At Purdue, Oren studied an eclectic mix of Political Science, Art and Design, Entrepreneurship, Viticulture, and Jewish Studies. Eventually he was approached by Jonathan with an interesting application of both form and function. “From what I’ve seen, business enterprise software suffers from an impressive lack of both. These issues are the result of years of decision-makers at large corporations with the luxury of not having to use the software they were purchasing.”\n\nNow Oren believes user interface has emerged as one of the most significant considerations for the future. “Technology has progressed to such an advanced stage that the bottleneck has become the connection between technology and the users. Computers now wait for us more than we wait for them.” By emphasizing simple and clean design practice, Oren hopes to create an interface that users will find intuitive and even addicting to use. “One day FoundOPS will be done when it does everything our users want and nothing else.”\n\nBeyond software, Oren loves spending time with his family and friends out on Shelter Island. An avid sailor, he claims his first crib was the v-berth (the triangle shaped bed located in the very front of a boat) on his father’s Cape Dory sailboat. When the snow falls outside the FoundOPS office, Oren dreams about skiing, but he’s concerned his techniques has suffered since he moved out to Indiana.\n\n</div>\n<div id=\"zachBg\"></div>\n<div id=\"zachImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\n<div id=\"zachDesc\">\n<div class=\"bigText\">\n\nZach Bright\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72290770\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/zbbright\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\n<div id=\"zachBar\"></div>\n<div class=\"greyText\">\n\nSenior Software Engineer\n\n</div>\nA die-hard Cubs fan, Zach hails from the suburbs of Chicago. At Purdue, Zach was a distinguished student of Computer Engineering, the president of his fraternity, all while working as a teaching assistant. Working with an entire fraternity of men or a class full of students taught Zach a great deal of patience. While Jon and Oren’s passion can create a great deal of excitement, we can always rely on Zach’s calming disposition to maintain order at FoundOPS.\n\nZach loves getting outside on a nice day and playing a few holes of golf. He’ll be happy where ever he is in the world as long he can tune in to watch the Cubs play.\n\n</div>\n<div id=\"andrewBg\"></div>\n<div id=\"andrewImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\n<div id=\"andrewDesc\">\n<div class=\"bigText\">\n\nAndrew Pohl\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=70782535\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/apohl1111\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\n<div id=\"andrewBar\"></div>\n<div class=\"greyText\">\n\nSilverlight Developer and Designer\n\n</div>\nAndrew grew up in rural Indiana on a farm which might have something to do with his strong work ethic. “I leave work not when I’m tired, but when I’m done.” After earning his degree from Purdue in Computer Graphics Technology, Andrew joined the FoundOPS team as a Silverlight developer and has been invaluable for creating the look and feel of the site.\n\nWhen he’s not working on the project, Andrew enjoys spending time outdoors and playing Ultimate Frisbee. Occasionally he can be found kicking back and watching an action movie or two. His goals are modest but quickly becoming fulfilled; to be successful at something he enjoys.\n\n</div>\n<div id=\"johnBg\"></div>\n<div id=\"johnImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\n<div id=\"johnDesc\">\n<div class=\"bigText\">\n\nJohn Mahoney\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=42714775\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\n<div id=\"johnBar\"></div>\n<div class=\"greyText\">\n\nSoftware Engineer\n\n</div>\nJohn was originally from Virginia before moving out to California to study aerospace engineering. Before joining the FoundOPS team, John worked in IT for a number of years. Nowadays, John is known as the algorithms guys and has been responsible for developing much of the logic that makes FoundOPS dispatching so efficient.\n\nIn his spare time, John can be found working with his hands on various construction projects. He also enjoys producing music. One day John hopes to turn his talents towards space exploration.\n\n</div>\n</div>','The Team','','inherit','open','open','','21-autosave','','','2011-09-23 12:26:59','2011-09-23 16:26:59','',21,'http://localhost:15880/2011/09/15/21-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(38,1,'2011-09-09 15:06:11','2011-09-09 19:06:11','lots of words will follow this\r\n\r\nword word word word word word word word word word word\r\n\r\nword word word word word word word word word word word word word word word word word word word word word\r\n\r\nword word word word word word word word word word','Another test post','','inherit','open','open','','19-revision-2','','','2011-09-09 15:06:11','2011-09-09 19:06:11','',19,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/09/19-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(39,1,'2011-09-08 15:30:03','2011-09-08 19:30:03','testing...ffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffffgggggggggggggggggggggggggggggggggkkkkkkkkkkkkk llllllllllllllllllllllllllllll kkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkk jjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjj hhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh fffffffffffffffffffffff','2nd test post jykylululhl gjgfjgfj','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision-5','','','2011-09-08 15:30:03','2011-09-08 19:30:03','',14,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/08/14-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(40,1,'2011-09-07 11:54:24','2011-09-07 15:54:24','Blah Blah Blah some words','First Test Post','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-2','','','2011-09-07 11:54:24','2011-09-07 15:54:24','',5,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/07/5-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(41,4,'2011-09-23 11:56:45','2011-09-23 15:56:45','Software companies tout the term ”enterprise grade” as an excuse for their application’s convoluted maze-like interfaces and grey forms designed circa 1990. Supposedly, it offer some unmatched level of stability, security, and scalability. In reality “consumer grade” technologies (such as Gmail) are easier to use, have enjoyed higher reliability, and are hassle free. FoundOPS is committed to “consumer grade” design and in this article I will discuss why your company should be too.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>How did enterprise and consumer design practice diverge?</strong></div>\r\nEnterprise giants software is merely a product of its upbringing. In the past, enterprise software design was steered by large corporate executives who enjoyed the luxury of never using the software they were spec’ing. While consumer marketed companies hired product managers and user experience and interface designers, enterprise companies pushed out features so ugly, only a developer’s mother could love them.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>The new wave of consumer grade design in the enterprise.</strong></div>\r\nBack in July of 2010, Aaron Levie, the CEO of Box.net, a company that produces business content management software for the enterprise, announced in a blog post that “Enterprise Software is Sexy Again”. Levie cited the new wave of enterprise software companies, including his own, PBWorks, Asana, and Workday, which have created software unlike anything the enterprise has seen before. These companies have all experienced great successes, inspiring fear in their multibillion dollar competition. A quick look at the websites, offices, and products of these companies and you’ll see a far greater resemblance to YouTube, Twitter, and Facebook then traditional enterprise companies. With a deeper examination of their product design, you’ll draw the same conclusion I have, that these companies have employed consumer grade design.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What’s the advantage for my business?</strong></div>\r\nOk, so it looks pretty, but beyond that, well designed software offers a number of advantages to its users.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Significantly shorter training times</strong> – For those with exposure to consumer-grade software like Gmail or Yahoo, learning how to use the next generation enterprise software takes minutes or hours, not days or weeks.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Higher efficiency</strong> – Do more with fewer clicks.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Leverage generation Y</strong> – The latest generation entering the job market has grown up around the Internet. If your old system doesn’t engage and take full advantage of your new hires’ talents, how can your company?</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Visualize your business</strong> - Modern visualization tools can give you live insights on your business.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Be Happier</strong> – Remember the copier scene in office space? (http://movieclips.com/Ndfb-office-space-movie-printer-beat-down/) If you’ve used traditional enterprise software, you can probably relate. You’re going to spend a fair bit of time on your enterprise system. Do you really want to that much time frustrated?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What is FoundOPS doing?</strong></div>\r\nFoundOPS was developed with a design focus from day 1. \r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>The best interface technologies</strong> -  We use Microsoft Silverlight and HTML5 to create the most immersive user experience possible.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>User-centric design</strong> - Participation from everyone who uses our system (managers, dispatchers, field technicians, your customers) is an integral part of our design process.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Design culture</strong> - We appreciate good design and place value on novel concepts like simplicity and organic interactions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOver the next months, consumer grade design will be permeating into all types of business applications. FoundOPS is strategically positioned to lead this new wave of design and revolutionize how people interact with their business applications. If you are interested in contributing to our design process, please consider joining our beta program at this <a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\" title=\"The Team\">link</a>.','Consumer Grade Design','','publish','open','open','','consumer-grade-design','','','2011-09-23 15:43:01','2011-09-23 19:43:01','',0,'http://localhost:55206/?p=41',0,'post','',0),(42,1,'2011-09-23 11:50:27','2011-09-23 15:50:27','Software companies tout the term ”enterprise grade” as an excuse for their application’s convoluted maze-like interfaces and grey forms designed circa 1990. Supposedly, it offer some unmatched level of stability, security, and scalability. In reality “consumer grade” technologies (such as Gmail) are easier to use, have enjoyed higher reliability, and are hassle free. FoundOPS is committed to “consumer grade” design and in this article I will discuss why your company should be too.\nHow did enterprise and consumer design practice diverge?\n\nEnterprise giants software is merely a product of its upbringing. In the past, enterprise software design was steered by large corporate executives who enjoyed the luxury of never using the software they were spec’ing. While consumer marketed companies hired product managers and user experience and interface designers, enterprise companies pushed out features so ugly, only a developer’s mother could love them.\nThe new wave of consumer grade design in the enterprise.\n\nBack in July of 2010, Aaron Levie, the CEO of Box.net, a company that produces business content management software for the enterprise, announced in a blog post that “Enterprise Software is Sexy Again”. Levie cited the new wave of enterprise software companies, including his own, PBWorks, Asana, and Workday, which have created software unlike anything the enterprise has seen before. These companies have all experienced great successes, inspiring fear in their multibillion dollar competition. A quick look at the websites, offices, and products of these companies and you’ll see a far greater resemblance to YouTube, Twitter, and Facebook then traditional enterprise companies. With a deeper examination of their product design, you’ll draw the same conclusion I have, that these companies have employed consumer grade design.\nWhat’s the advantage for my business?\n\nOk, so it looks pretty, but beyond that, well designed software offers a number of advantages to its users.\nSignificantly shorter training times – For those with exposure to consumer-grade software like Gmail or Yahoo, learning how to use the next generation enterprise software takes minutes or hours, not days or weeks.\nHigher efficiency – Do more with fewer clicks.\nLeverage generation Y – The latest generation entering the job market has grown up around the Internet. If your old system doesn’t engage and take full advantage of your new hires’ talents, how can your company?\nVisualize your business - Modern visualization tools can give you live insights on your business.\nBe Happier – Remember the copier scene in office space? (http://movieclips.com/Ndfb-office-space-movie-printer-beat-down/) If you’ve used traditional enterprise software, you can probably relate. You’re going to spend a fair bit of time on your enterprise system. Do you really want to that much time frustrated?\n\nWhat is FoundOPS doing?\n\nFoundOPS was developed with a design focus from day 1. \n\nThe best interface technologies -  We use Microsoft Silverlight and HTML5 to create the most immersive user experience possible.\n\nUser-centric design - Participation from everyone who uses our system (managers, dispatchers, field technicians, your customers) is an integral part of our design process.\n\nDesign culture - We appreciate good design and place value on novel concepts like simplicity and organic interactions.\n\n\nOver the next months, consumer grade design will be permeating into all types of business applications. FoundOPS is strategically positioned to lead this new wave of design and revolutionize how people interact with their business applications. If you are interested in contributing to our design process, please consider joining our beta program at this link.','Consumer Grade Design','','inherit','open','open','','41-revision','','','2011-09-23 11:50:27','2011-09-23 15:50:27','',41,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/41-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(43,1,'2011-09-23 11:57:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2011-09-23 11:57:04','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost:55206/?p=43',0,'post','',0),(44,3,'2011-09-23 12:06:12','2011-09-23 16:06:12','There is a transformational shift occurring in technology. Organizations are cutting back their IT departments, business managers are rapidly deploying solutions, and people are all buzzing about the cloud. In this article I will try to address the following questions: what the cloud and “software as a service” is, why businesses are racing to the cloud, and what FoundOPS’ role is in this technological shift.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What is the cloud?</strong></div>\r\nThe cloud is a method of delivering computing and storage through the internet. An important term for the cloud is “software as a service” (SaaS). SaaS is an extension of the cloud that allows for the delivery of software through the internet. Gmail, Facebook, and Salesforce are all examples of software delivered over the internet and SaaS.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why are businesses racing to the cloud?</strong></div>\r\nSoftware as a service replaces the need for on premise servers by centralizing them to one place. Businesses are racing to the cloud because SaaS brings a long list of benefits.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>There is no need to purchase servers or server equipment. </li>\r\n	<li>Hosting and maintenance are managed by the service provider and built into one price; eliminating surprise problems and surprise consultant expenses.</li>\r\n	<li>There is little or no start-up costs and capital investment required for cloud based systems.</li>\r\n	<li>Cloud servers securely share resources and turn them on and off as needed. That is how cloud computing uses 95% lower power consumption than traditional on premise systems.</li>\r\n	<li>Cloud based systems are accessible anywhere there is an Internet connection. If your computer disappears or crashes, your data will still be available and secure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What is FoundOPS role?</strong></div>\r\nWe are committed to providing the latest and most effective technology. That is why all of FoundOPS services are provided through the cloud and as software as a service.\r\n\r\nA couple of interesting facts about our service:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Our software runs on Microsoft Azure’s infrastructure. Azure boasts 99.9% up-time and near infinite redundancy. Azure is the same platform Microsoft uses to host it’s own services (Hotmail, Windows Live, Office 365).</li>\r\n	<li>Cost savings from the cloud allow us to charge less than half of what our competitors charge. New businesses can now take advantage of technology they previously could not afford.</li>\r\n	<li>FoundOPS rates are all inclusive. Along with hosting, maintenance, and automatic daily backups, support and updates are also built into our pricing.</li>\r\n	<li>FoundOPS services can be rapidly deployed and therefore are quick to value. Services can easily be scaled up or down without penalty.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nIt is no surprise companies are quickly moving to the cloud. FoundOPS is here to help the service industry take advantage of this amazing technology. If you are interested in being part of our beta program please sign up <a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\" title=\"The Team\">here</a>.','Harness The Cloud','','publish','open','open','','harness-the-cloud','','','2011-09-23 13:08:22','2011-09-23 17:08:22','',0,'http://localhost:55206/?p=44',0,'post','',0),(45,1,'2011-09-23 12:05:45','2011-09-23 16:05:45','There is a transformational shift occurring in technology. Organizations are cutting back their IT departments, business managers are rapidly deploying solutions, and people are all buzzing about the cloud. In this article I will try to address the following questions: what the cloud and “software as a service” is, why businesses are racing to the cloud, and what FoundOPS’ role is in this technological shift.\n\n<div id=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What is the cloud?</strong></div>\nThe cloud is a method of delivering computing and storage through the internet. An important term for the cloud is “software as a service” (SaaS). SaaS is an extension of the cloud that allows for the delivery of software through the internet. Gmail, Facebook, and Salesforce are all examples of software delivered over the internet and SaaS.\n\n<div id=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why are businesses racing to the cloud?</strong></div>\nSoftware as a service replaces the need for on premise servers by centralizing them to one place. Businesses are racing to the cloud because SaaS brings a long list of benefits.\n<ul>\n	<li>There is no need to purchase servers or server equipment. </li>\n\n	<li>Hosting and maintenance are managed by the service provider and built into one price; e