w businesses can now take advantage of technology they previously could not afford.</li>\r\n	<li>FoundOPS rates are all inclusive. Along with hosting, maintenance, and automatic daily backups, support and updates are also built into our pricing.</li>\r\n	<li>FoundOPS services can be rapidly deployed and therefore are quick to value. Services can easily be scaled up or down without penalty.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nIt is no surprise companies are quickly moving to the cloud. FoundOPS is here to help the service industry take advantage of this amazing technology. If you are interested in being part of our beta program please sign up <a href=\"<?php echo blogLink?>/beta\" title=\"The Team\">here</a>.','The Cloud','','inherit','open','open','','44-revision-3','','','2011-09-23 12:06:37','2011-09-23 16:06:37','',44,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/44-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(48,5,'2011-09-23 12:11:49','2011-09-23 16:11:49','If your business is using an outdated operations software, or worse, still using a manual system then you are missing out on massive efficiency gains. All sized businesses are quickly realizing that without investment in technology, it is impossible to stay competitive.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why is efficiency so essential to small and medium sized businesses?</strong></div>\r\nEveryone knows that efficiency is a good thing. Yet proportionally, larger business outspend small businesses on efficiency investments. While the return on investment for small and medium sized businesses has a few less zeros tacked on, it is far more important. Small and medium businesses have less resources compared to large corporations; their ability to use them efficiently is often the determination for their success and growth. \r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why is now the right time for efficiency?</strong></div>\r\nEconomic turns have caused many businesses to buckle down. Improving efficiency is an important way to ensure your survival. Operations software can not only save your business money on fuel, labor, and other expenses, it can also increase your competitive advantage and help you to retain your current customers while adding new ones. Additionally, recent technology developments are making efficiency software more attainable then ever. With cloud computing and “Software as a Service”, large upfront investments have been replaced with sensible monthly subscriptions. (You can read more about cloud computing and SaaS <a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/2011/09/23/harness-the-cloud/\">here</a>)\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What can FoundOPS do for your efficiency?</strong></div>\r\nFoundOPS has developed an system that can radically improve your business operations.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Advanced routing algorithms</strong> - In a single click our software will generate routes that make your fleet more efficient, reducing fuel consumption, vehicle usage, and labor costs.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Data entry</strong> - Even in small and medium sized businesses, data entry can be a major administrative cost. With FoundOPS, your entire team can contribute customer and service data, whenever and where ever it is collected.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Automatic invoicing</strong> -  By integrating with Quickbooks you can ensure that every job makes it to an invoice, dramatically increasing your collection rates.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Actionable business intelligence</strong> - Use insights gained from your data to make better decisions about the future of your business.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\nLets face it, we all have days where we have wished there were just a few more hours. Running a business is no simple task (trust us we know). Being more efficient is a goal of every business owner. FoundOPS can make your business dramatically more efficient and if you’re interested in seeing for yourself, sign up for our beta program <a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">here</a>.','Efficiency Reimagined','','publish','open','open','','efficiency-reimagined','','','2011-09-23 13:10:56','2011-09-23 17:10:56','',0,'http://localhost:55206/?p=48',0,'post','',0),(49,1,'2011-09-23 12:11:12','2011-09-23 16:11:12','If your business is using an outdated operations software, or worse, still using a manual system then you are missing out on massive efficiency gains. All sized businesses are quickly realizing that without investment in technology, it is impossible to stay competitive.\n\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why is efficiency so essential to small and medium sized businesses?</strong></div>\nEveryone knows that efficiency is a good thing. Yet proportionally, larger business outspend small businesses on efficiency investments. While the return on investment for small and medium sized businesses has a few less zeros tacked on, it is far more important. Small and medium businesses have less resources compared to large corporations; their ability to use them efficiently is often the determination for their success and growth. \n\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why is now the right time for efficiency?</strong></div>\nEconomic turns have caused many businesses to buckle down. Improving efficiency is an important way to ensure your survival. Operations software can not only save your business money on fuel, labor, and other expenses, it can also increase your competitive advantage and help you to retain your current customers while adding new ones. Additionally, recent technology developments are making efficiency software more attainable then ever. With cloud computing and “Software as a Service”, large upfront investments have been replaced with sensible monthly subscriptions. (You can read more about cloud computing and SaaS <a href=\"http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/the-cloud/\">here</a>)\n\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What can FoundOPS do for your efficiency?</strong></div>\nFoundOPS has developed an system that can radically improv