fice for the occasional bike ride or run. He’ll also read anything he can get his hands if he thinks it will give him a bit of knowledge. One day Jonathan hopes to have some time to travel the world and just meet people but for now he is happy right where he is.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nOren Shatken\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72288581\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/OrenShatken\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nCofounder and President, Product\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nThe son of an artist and an architect, Oren has always been torn between the worlds of form and function. At Purdue, Oren studied an eclectic mix of Political Science, Art and Design, Entrepreneurship, Viticulture, and Jewish Studies. Eventually he was approached by Jonathan with an interesting application of both form and function. “From what I’ve seen, business enterprise software suffers from an impressive lack of both. These issues are the result of years of decision-makers at large corporations with the luxury of not having to use the software they were purchasing.”\r\n\r\nNow Oren believes user interface has emerged as one of the most significant considerations for the future. “Technology has progressed to such an advanced stage that the bottleneck has become the connection between technology and the users. Computers now wait for us more than we wait for them.” By emphasizing simple and clean design practice, Oren hopes to create an interface that users will find intuitive and even addicting to use. “One day FoundOPS will be done when it does everything our users want and nothing else.”\r\n\r\nBeyond software, Oren loves spending time with his family and friends out on Shelter Island. An avid sailor, he claims his first crib was the v-berth (the triangle shaped bed located in the very front of a boat) on his father’s Cape Dory sailboat. When the snow falls outside the FoundOPS office, Oren dreams about skiing, but he’s concerned his techniques has suffered since he moved out to Indiana.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nZach Bright\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72290770\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/zbbright\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSenior Software Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nA die-hard Cubs fan, Zach hails from the suburbs of Chicago. At Purdue, Zach was a distinguished student of Computer Engineering, the president of his fraternity, all while working as a teaching assistant. Working with an entire fraternity of men or a class full of students taught Zach a great deal of patience. While Jon and Oren’s passion can create a great deal of excitement, we can always rely on Zach’s calming disposition to maintain order at FoundOPS.\r\n\r\nZach loves getting outside on a nice day and playing a few holes of golf. He’ll be happy where ever he is in the world as long he can tune in to watch the Cubs play.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nAndrew Pohl\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=70782535\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/apohl1111\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSilverlight Developer and Designer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nAndrew grew up in rural Indiana on a farm which might have something to do with his strong work ethic. “I leave work not when I’m tired, but when I’m done.” After earning his degree from Purdue in Computer Graphics Technology, Andrew joined the FoundOPS team as a Silverlight developer and has been invaluable for creating the look and feel of the site.\r\n\r\nWhen he’s not working on the project, Andrew enjoys spending time outdoors and playing Ultimate Frisbee. Occasionally he can be found kicking back and watching an action movie or two. His goals are modest but quickly becoming fulfilled; to be successful at something he enjoys.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nJohn Mahoney\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=42714775\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSoftware Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJohn was originally from Virginia before moving out to California to study aerospace engineering. Before joining the FoundOPS team, John worked in IT for a number of years. Nowadays, John is known as the algorithms guys and has been responsible for developing much of the logic that makes FoundOPS dispatching so efficient.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time, John can be found working with his hands on various construction projects. He also enjoys producing music. One day John hopes to turn his talents towards space exploration.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','The Team','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-22','','','2011-09-23 12:35:48','2011-09-23 16:35:48','',21,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/21-revision-22/',0,'revision','',0),(62,1,'2011-09-23 12:36:29','2011-09-23 16:36:29','<div style=\"position: relative; top: -55px; left: 297px; background: none; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px;\">\r\n<div id=\"navBoxTeam\">\r\n            <ul class=\"tabs\">\r\n                <li style=\"border-top:none;\"><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>\">Home</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">FoundOPS</a></li>    \r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">About Us</a>\r\n                    <ul class=\"subNav\">\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">The Team</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/values\">Our Values</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/jobs\">Jobs</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>/Home/ContactUs\">Contact Us</a></li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>\">Blog</a></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The Team</h1>\r\n<div class=\"titleBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"titleText\">We’re young, committed, and lean (in our development methodology, not necessarily our body types).</div>\r\n<div id=\"jonBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nJonathan Perl\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=40656805\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/jon_perl\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nFounder and President, Technology\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJon started FoundOPS because of the great deal of potential he sees for the future for technology. He believes that the next revolution belongs to small business. “Everyday we see technology breaking down barriers and making more resources available.” FoundOPS hopes to help small businesses harness the incredible resources and opportunities that are now available to them.\r\n\r\nAt 21, Jonathan may be young, but he is no newcomer to the world of business software. During high school Jonathan got his start working as software consultant for the service industry. In college, he knew the potential that existed for a small business software platform and began working on a solution. The prototypes he developed have become the precursor to FoundOPS.\r\n\r\nWhen asked what he likes to do in his free time, Jonathan responds “Free time?” Despite his borderline obsessive commitment to FoundOPS, Jonathan still manages to sneak out of the office for the occasional bike ride or run. He’ll also read anything he can get his hands if he thinks it will give him a bit of knowledge. One day Jonathan hopes to have some time to travel the world and just meet people but for now he is happy right where he is.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nOren Shatken\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72288581\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/OrenShatken\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nCofounder and President, Product\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nThe son of an artist and an architect, Oren has always been torn between the worlds of form and function. At Purdue, Oren studied an eclectic mix of Political Science, Art and Design, Entrepreneurship, Viticulture, and Jewish Studies. Eventually he was approached by Jonathan with an interesting application of both form and function. “From what I’ve seen, business enterprise software suffers from an impressive lack of both. These issues are the result of years of decision-makers at large corporations with the luxury of not having to use the software they were purchasing.”\r\n\r\nNow Oren believes user interface has emerged as one of the most significant considerations for the future. “Technology has progressed to such an advanced stage that the bottleneck has become the connection between technology and the users. Computers now wait for us more than we wait for them.” By emphasizing simple and clean design practice, Oren hopes to create an interface that users will find intuitive and even addicting to use. “One day FoundOPS will be done when it does everything our users want and nothing else.”\r\n\r\nBeyond software, Oren loves spending time with his family and friends out on Shelter Island. An avid sailor, he claims his first crib was the v-berth (the triangle shaped bed located in the very front of a boat) on his father’s Cape Dory sailboat. When the snow falls outside the FoundOPS office, Oren dreams about skiing, but he’s concerned his techniques has suffered since he moved out to Indiana.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nZach Bright\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72290770\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/zbbright\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSenior Software Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nA die-hard Cubs fan, Zach hails from the suburbs of Chicago. At Purdue, Zach was a distinguished student of Computer Engineering, the president of his fraternity, all while working as a teaching assistant. Working with an entire fraternity of men or a class full of students taught Zach a great deal of patience. While Jon and Oren’s passion can create a great deal of excitement, we can always rely on Zach’s calming disposition to maintain order at FoundOPS.\r\n\r\nZach loves getting outside on a nice day and playing a few holes of golf. He’ll be happy where ever he is in the world as long he can tune in to watch the Cubs play.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nAndrew Pohl\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=70782535\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/apohl1111\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSilverlight Developer and Designer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nAndrew grew up in rural Indiana on a farm which might have something to do with his strong work ethic. “I leave work not when I’m tired, but when I’m done.” After earning his degree from Purdue in Computer Graphics Technology, Andrew joined the FoundOPS team as a Silverlight developer and has been invaluable for creating the look and feel of the site.\r\n\r\nWhen he’s not working on the project, Andrew enjoys spending time outdoors and playing Ultimate Frisbee. Occasionally he can be found kicking back and watching an action movie or two. His goals are modest but quickly becoming fulfilled; to be successful at something he enjoys.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nJohn Mahoney\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=42714775\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSoftware Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJohn was originally from Virginia before moving out to California to study aerospace engineering. Before joining the FoundOPS team, John worked in IT for a number of years. Nowadays, John is known as the algorithms guys and has been responsible for developing much of the logic that makes FoundOPS dispatching so efficient.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time, John can be found working with his hands on various construction projects. He also enjoys producing music. One day John hopes to turn his talents towards space exploration.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','The Team','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-23','','','2011-09-23 12:36:29','2011-09-23 16:36:29','',21,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/21-revision-23/',0,'revision','',0),(63,1,'2011-09-23 12:38:16','2011-09-23 16:38:16','<div id=\"values\">\r\n<div id=\"navBoxTeam\">\r\n            <ul class=\"tabs\">\r\n                <li style=\"border-top:none;\"><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>\">Home</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">FoundOPS</a></li>    \r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">About Us</a>\r\n                    <ul class=\"subNav\">\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">The Team</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/values\">Our Values</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/jobs\">Jobs</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>/Home/ContactUs\">Contact Us</a></li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>\">Blog</a></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Our Values</h1>\r\n<div class=\"valueTitleBar\" style=\"color:#991A36;\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"valueTitleText\">Uncompromising.</div>\r\n<div id=\"EnvironmentBg\"></div>\r\n<h1><img id=\"EnvironmentImg\" src=\"http://localhost:31820/Content/Environment.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<div id=\"EnvironmentDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">Environment</div>\r\n<div id=\"EnvironmentBar\"></div>\r\n<ul class=\"ShiftLeft\">\r\n	<li>Today, a company’s value is measured in broader terms than just their balance sheet. We feel strongly that our net gains to the greater good are just as important as our continued growth. The decisions we make everyday reflect this commitment.</li>\r\n	<li>Our service enables our clients to become dramatically greener.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bullet\">Cloud computing has up to a 95% smaller carbon footprint then on-site hardware. It permits lower power consumption, more efficient use of resources, and easier access to green upgrades.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"bullet\">Computer optimized routes increase efficiency and reduce vehicle emissions.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"bullet\">Many of our clients have transitioned towards paperless offices.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>We’ve developed software solutions for emerging Green businesses such as biodiesel producers to support their growth.</li>\r\n	<li>Internally, our corporate initiatives decrease our personal environmental impact.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bullet\">Encouraging employees to ride bicycles to work.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"bullet\">Use of environmentally friendly cleaning products.</li>\r\n	<li class=\"bullet\">Dramatic reduction of paper and disposable products in the office.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"AccessabilityBg\"></div>\r\n<h1><img id=\"AccessabilityImg\" src=\"http://localhost:31820/Content/Accessability.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<div id=\"AccessabilityDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">Accessibility</div>\r\n<div id=\"AccessabilityBar\"></div>\r\n<ul class=\"ShiftLeft\">\r\n	<li>Since we started developing FoundOPS, our goal for our platform has been to make the same quality and customization of a traditional enterprise solutions available to any business. We have identified the barriers that previously prevented small businesses from employing an enterprise system.\r\n<ul class=\"ShiftLeft\">	<li><strong>Hardware</strong></li>\r\n	<li>On site servers require large initial investments, continual maintenance, professional IT support, and are difficult to scale. Our solution is served on Microsoft’s Azure Cloud platform which boasts an unprecedented 99.9% reliability coupled with industry leading security and backup features. This means that our clients will never be required to make any investments in servers. Furthermore, our Microsoft Silverlight application can be accessed through any major Internet browser on any PC or Mac. In all likely hood, this means your existing computers are more than sufficient for your needs. Finally, if you use our mobile application, we have chosen Google’s Android operating system which currently offers the largest selection of (and least expensive) mobile phones and wireless providers.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Customized Solutions</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Larger businesses have the luxury of investing hundreds of thousands of dollars into custom enterprise solutions. Mid-size businesses can afford to have IT professionals customize existing systems or mesh together a number of applications. Until now, small businesses were forced to accept software as is. FoundOPS developed its application around the idea that anyone should be able to customize the system.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Training</strong></li>\r\n	<li>By focusing on simple and intuitive interfaces, we think we’ve dramatically cut down the learning curve on enterprise software. While traditional solutions offer weekend seminars and classes in their systems, we’re confident that anyone who has learned how to access their email can learn how to operate our system. This removes down time and training costs, which allows you to focus on running your business.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Price</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Finally, we think we’ve come up with highly competitive pricing for our offering. When you add on the savings you’ll see from hardware, personnel, IT support, and training/down time, FoundOPS can be saving your business tens of thousands of dollars a year.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"CommunityBg\"></div>\r\n<h1><img id=\"CommunityImg\" src=\"http://localhost:31820/Content/Community.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<div id=\"CommunityDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">Community</div>\r\n<div id=\"CommunityBar\"></div>\r\n<p>Located in West Lafayette, Indiana, the home of Purdue University, FoundOPS enjoys close ties with its community. Many of our employees were and continue to be proud Boilermakers. In addition, each year, FoundOPS offers a number of internship opportunities to the best and brightest Purdue students. We support local commerce and enjoy eating local produce and drinking local beer.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"IntegrityBg\"></div>\r\n<h1><img id=\"IntegrityImg\" src=\"http://localhost:31820/Content/Integrity.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<div id=\"IntegrityDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">Integrity</div>\r\n<div id=\"IntegrityBar\"></div>\r\n<p>We’re still a small business ourselves with ambitions as lofty as those of our clients. However in our pursuit of smart growth, we vow to continue to maintain the highest standards of integrity and responsibility. In conjunction with the institutional measures we employ, we pride ourselves on the atmosphere of responsibility we’ve been able to maintain throughout the entire company. At FoundOPS, the ‘buck’ stops on every single employee’s desk.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Our Values','','publish','open','open','','values','','','2011-09-23 12:38:38','2011-09-23 16:38:38','',0,'http://localhost:55206/?page_id=63',0,'page','',0),(64,1,'2011-09-23 12:38:03','2011-09-23 16:38:03','','Our Values','','inherit','open','open','','63-revision','','','2011-09-23 12:38:03','2011-09-23 16:38:03','',63,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/63-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(65,1,'20