            <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>\">Blog</a></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n<h1 class=\"betaTitle\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Beta</h1>\r\n<div class=\"betaTitleBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"jobsTitleText\">\r\n<p>Experienced entrepreneurs say that you fall in love with a problem first, then you innovate a solution. At FoundOPS, the problems we’ve fallen in love with are those facing small field service companies. Where are my technicians? What job am I going to next? Have all of my customers paid me? If you’ve ever managed a service team, you know how difficult these problems can be. Wouldn’t it be great if there was a system that helped you keep track of everything? It would be easy to setup and easier to use. You would be able log in through your computer and see exactly where your team was. Assigning jobs would be as simple as dragging and dropping. Technicians would see their next jobs on their mobile phones and be able to use turn-by-turn navigation to get their fast. And it would be cloud based so your data would be secure and you could access it from anywhere with an Internet connection. </p>\r\n<p>Sounds simple enough, right? So that’s what we’ve set out to do. It’s taken some time, a few pivots, but now we’re starting to see a pretty good system take face. However in order for it to become a great system, we know we need your help. Did we make the buttons on our mobile app big enough for you to use with your work gloves on? Is there some feature you just have to have? If shaping the next generation of service software sounds like something you might be interested in, complete the form below and we’ll get in contact with you.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Beta','','inherit','open','open','','69-revision-5','','','2011-09-23 12:53:39','2011-09-23 16:53:39','',69,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/69-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(76,1,'2011-09-23 12:11:49','2011-09-23 16:11:49','If your business is using an outdated operations software, or worse, still using a manual system then you are missing out on massive efficiency gains. All sized businesses are quickly realizing that without investment in technology, it is impossible to stay competitive.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why is efficiency so essential to small and medium sized businesses?</strong></div>\r\nEveryone knows that efficiency is a good thing. Yet proportionally, larger business outspend small businesses on efficiency investments. While the return on investment for small and medium sized businesses has a few less zeros tacked on, it is far more important. Small and medium businesses have less resources compared to large corporations; their ability to use them efficiently is often the determination for their success and growth. \r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why is now the right time for efficiency?</strong></div>\r\nEconomic turns have caused many businesses to buckle down. Improving efficiency is an important way to ensure your survival. Operations software can not only save your business money on fuel, labor, and other expenses, it can also increase your competitive advantage and help you to retain your current customers while adding new ones. Additionally, recent technology developments are making efficiency software more attainable then ever. With cloud computing and “Software as a Service”, large upfront investments have been replaced with sensible monthly subscriptions. (You can read more about cloud computing and SaaS <a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/2011/09/23/the-cloud/\">here</a>)\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What can FoundOPS do for your efficiency?</strong></div>\r\nFoundOPS has developed an system that can radically improve your business operations.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Advanced routing algorithms</strong> - In a single click our software will generate routes that make your fleet more efficient, reducing fuel consumption, vehicle usage, and labor costs.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Data entry</strong> - Even in small and medium sized businesses, data entry can be a major administrative cost. With FoundOPS, your entire team can contribute customer and service data, whenever and where ever it is collected.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Automatic invoicing</strong> -  By integrating with Quickbooks you can ensure that every job makes it to an invoice, dramatically increasing your collection rates.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Actionable business intelligence</strong> - Use insights gained from your data to make better decisions about the future of your business.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\nLets face it, we all have days where we have wished there were just a few more hours. Running a business is no simple task (trust us we know). Being more efficient is a goal of every business owner. FoundOPS can make your business dramatically more efficient and if you’re interested in seeing for yourself, sign up for our beta program <a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">here</a>.','Efficiency is Key','','inherit','open','open','','48-revision-2','','','2011-09-23 12:11:49','2011-09-23 16:11:49','',48,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/48-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(77,1,'2011-09-23 12:12:07','2011-09-23 16:12:07','There is a transformational shift occurring in technology. Organizations are cutting back their IT departments, business managers are rapidly deploying solutions, and people are all buzzing about the cloud. In this article I will try to address the following questions: what the cloud and “software as a service” is, why businesses are racing to the cloud, and what FoundOPS’ role is in this technological shift.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What is the cloud?</strong></div>\r\nThe cloud is a method of delivering computing and storage through the internet. An important term for the cloud is “software as a service” (SaaS). SaaS is an extension of the cloud that allows for the delivery of software through the internet. Gmail, Facebook, and Salesforce are all examples of software delivered over the internet and SaaS.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why are businesses racing to the cloud?</strong></div>\r\nSoftware as a service replaces the need for on premise servers by centralizing them to one place. Businesses are racing to the cloud because SaaS brings a long list of benefits.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>There is no need to purchase servers or server equipment. </li>\r\n	<li>Hosting and maintenance are managed by the service provider and built into one price; eliminating surprise problems and surprise consultant expenses.</li>\r\n	<li>There is little or no start-up costs and capital investment required for cloud based systems.</li>\r\n	<li>Cloud servers securely share resources and turn them on and off as needed. That is how cloud computing uses 95% lower power consumption than traditional on premise systems.</li>\r\n	<li>Cloud based systems are accessible anywhere there is an Internet connection. If your computer disappears or crashes, your data will still be available and secure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What is FoundOPS role?</strong></div>\r\nWe are committed to providing the latest and most effective technology. That is why all of FoundOPS services are provided through the cloud and as software as a service.\r\n\r\nA couple of interesting facts about our service:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Our software runs on Microsoft Azure’s infrastructure. Azure boasts 99.9% up-time and near infinite redundancy. Azure is the same platform Microsoft uses to host it’s own services (Hotmail, Windows Live, Office 365).</li>\r\n	<li>Cost savings from the cloud allow us to charge less than half of what our competitors charge. New businesses can now take advantage of technology they previously could not afford.</li>\r\n	<li>FoundOPS rates are all inclusive. Along with hosting, maintenance, and automatic daily backups, support and updates are also built into our pricing.</li>\r\n	<li>FoundOPS services can be rapidly deployed and therefore are quick to value. Services can easily be scaled up or down without penalty.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nIt is no surprise companies are quickly moving to the cloud. FoundOPS is here to help the service industry take advantage of this amazing technology. If you are interested in being part of our beta program please sign up <a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\" title=\"The Team\">here</a>.','The Cloud','','inherit','open','open','','44-revision-5','','','2011-09-23 12:12:07','2011-09-23 16:12:07','',44,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/44-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(78,1,'2011-09-23 13:07:40','2011-09-23 17:07:40','If your business is using an outdated operations software, or worse, still using a manual system then you are missing out on massive efficiency gains. All sized businesses are quickly realizing that without investment in technology, it is impossible to stay competitive.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why is efficiency so essential to small and medium sized businesses?</strong></div>\r\nEveryone knows that efficiency is a good thing. Yet proportionally, larger business outspend small businesses on efficiency investments. While the return on investment for small and medium sized businesses has a few less zeros tacked on, it is far more important. Small and medium businesses have less resources compared to large corporations; their ability to use them efficiently is often the determination for their success and growth. \r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>Why is now the right time for efficiency?</strong></div>\r\nEconomic turns have caused many businesses to buckle down. Improving efficiency is an important way to ensure your survival. Operations software can not only save your business money on fuel, labor, and other expenses, it can also increase your competitive advantage and help you to retain your current customers while adding new ones. Additionally, recent technology developments are making efficiency software more attainable then ever. With cloud computing and “Software as a Service”, large upfront investments have been replaced with sensible monthly subscriptions. (You can read more about cloud computing and SaaS <a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/2011/09/23/the-cloud/\">here</a>)\r\n\r\n<div class=\"lightBlue\"><strong>What can FoundOPS do for your efficiency?</strong></div>\r\nFoundOPS has developed an system that can radically improve your business operations.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Advanced routing algorithms</strong> - In a single click our software will generate routes that make your fleet more efficient, reducing fuel consumption, vehicle usage, and labor costs.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Data entry</strong> - Even in small and medium sized businesses, data entry can be a major administrative cost. With FoundOPS, your entire team can contribute customer and service data, whenever and where ever it is collected.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Automatic invoicing</strong> -  By integrating with Quickbooks you can ensure that every job makes it to an invoice, dramatically increasing your collection rates.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Actionable business intelligence</strong> - Use insights gained from your data to make better decisions about the future of your business.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\nLets face it, we all have days where we have wished there were just a few more hours. Running a business is no simple task (trust us we know). Being more efficient is a goal of every business owner. FoundOPS can make your business dramatically more efficient and if you’re interested in seeing for yourself, sign up for our beta program <a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">here</a>.','Efficiency Reimagined','','inherit','open','open','','48-revision-3','','','2011-09-23 13:07:40','2011-09-23 17:07:40','',48,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/48-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(79,1,'2011-09-23 12:37:03','2011-09-23 16:37:03','<div style=\"position: relative; top: -55px; left: 297px; background: none; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px;\">\r\n    <div id=\"navBoxTeam\">\r\n            <ul class=\"tabs\">\r\n                <li style=\"border-top:none;\"><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>\">Home</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">FoundOPS</a></li>    \r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">About Us</a>\r\n                    <ul class=\"subNav\">\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">The Team</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/values\">Our Values</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/jobs\">Jobs</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>/Home/ContactUs\">Contact Us</a></li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>\">Blog</a></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The Team</h1>\r\n<div class=\"titleBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"titleText\">We’re young, committed, and lean (in our development methodology, not necessarily our body types).</div>\r\n<div id=\"jonBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nJonathan Perl\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=40656805\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/jon_perl\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nFounder and President, Technology\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJon started FoundOPS because of the great deal of potential he sees for the future for technology. He believes that the next revolution belongs to small business. “Everyday we see technology breaking down barriers and making more resources available.” FoundOPS hopes to help small businesses harness the incredible resources and opportunities that are now available to them.\r\n\r\nAt 21, Jonathan may be young, but he is no newcomer to the world of business software. During high school Jonathan got his start working as software consultant for the service industry. In college, he knew the potential that existed for a small business software platform and began working on a solution. The prototypes he developed have become the precursor to FoundOPS.\r\n\r\nWhen asked what he likes to do in his free time, Jonathan responds “Free time?” Despite his borderline obsessive commitment to FoundOPS, Jonathan still manages to sneak out of the office for the occasional bike ride or run. He’ll also read anything he can get his hands if he thinks it will give him a bit of knowledge. One day Jonathan hopes to have some time to travel the world and just meet people but for now he is happy right where he is.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nOren Shatken\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72288581\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/OrenShatken\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nCofounder and President, Product\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nThe son of an artist and an architect, Oren has always been torn between the worlds of form and function. At Purdue, Oren studied an eclectic mix of Political Science, Art and Design, Entrepreneurship, Viticulture, and Jewish Studies. Eventually he was approached by Jonathan with an interesting application of both form and function. “From what I’ve seen, business enterprise software suffers from an impressive lack of both. These issues are the result of years of decision-makers at large corporations with the luxury of not having to use the software they were purchasing.”\r\n\r\nNow Oren believes user interface has emerged as one of the most significant considerations for the future. “Technology has progressed to such an advanced stage that the bottleneck has become the connection between technology and the users. Computers now wait for us more than we wait for them.” By emphasizing simple and clean design practice, Oren hopes to create an interface that users will find intuitive and even addicting to use. “One day FoundOPS will be done when it does everything our users want and nothing else.”\r\n\r\nBeyond software, Oren loves spending time with his family and friends out on Shelter Island. An avid sailor, he claims his first crib was the v-berth (the triangle shaped bed located in the very front of a boat) on his father’s Cape Dory sailboat. When the snow falls outside the FoundOPS office, Oren dreams about skiing, but he’s concerned his techniques has suffered since he moved out to Indiana.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nZach Bright\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72290770\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/zbbright\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSenior Software Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nA die-hard Cubs fan, Zach hails from the suburbs of Chicago. At Purdue, Zach was a distinguished student of Computer Engineering, the president of his fraternity, all while working as a teaching assistant. Working with an entire fraternity of men or a class full of students taught Zach a great deal of patience. While Jon and Oren’s passion can create a great deal of excitement, we can always rely on Zach’s calming disposition to maintain order at FoundOPS.\r\n\r\nZach loves getting outside on a nice day and playing a few holes of golf. He’ll be happy where ever he is in the world as long he can tune in to watch the Cubs play.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nAndrew Pohl\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=70782535\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/apohl1111\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSilverlight Developer and Designer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nAndrew grew up in rural Indiana on a farm which might have something to do with his strong work ethic. “I leave work not when I’m tired, but when I’m done.” After earning his degree from Purdue in Computer Graphics Technology, Andrew joined the FoundOPS team as a Silverlight developer and has been invaluable for creating the look and feel of the site.\r\n\r\nWhen he’s not working on the project, Andrew enjoys spending time outdoors and playing Ultimate Frisbee. Occasionally he can be found kicking back and watching an action movie or two. His goals are modest but quickly becoming fulfilled; to be successful at something he enjoys.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nJohn Mahoney\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=42714775\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSoftware Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJohn was originally from Virginia before moving out to California to study aerospace engineering. Before joining the FoundOPS team, John worked in IT for a number of years. Nowadays, John is known as the algorithms guys and has been responsible for developing much of the logic that makes FoundOPS dispatching so efficient.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time, John can be found working with his hands on various construction projects. He also enjoys producing music. One day John hopes to turn his talents towards space exploration.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','The Team','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-24','','','2011-09-23 12:37:03','2011-09-23 16:37:03','',21,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/21-revision-24/',0,'revision','',0),(80,1,'2011-09-23 13:16:41','2011-09-23 17:16:41','<div style=\"position: relative; top: -55px; left: 297px; background: none; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px;\">\r\n    <div id=\"navBoxTeam\">\r\n            <ul class=\"tabs\">\r\n                <li style=\"border-top:none;\"><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>\">Home</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">FoundOPS</a></li>    \r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">About Us</a>\r\n                    <ul class=\"subNav\">\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">The Team</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/values\">Our Values</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/jobs\">Jobs</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>/Home/ContactUs\">Contact Us</a></li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>\">Blog</a></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The Team</h1>\r\n<div class=\"titleBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"titleText\">We’re young, committed, and lean (in our development methodology, not necessarily our body types).</div>\r\n<div id=\"jonBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nJonathan Perl\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=40656805\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/jon_perl\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nFounder and President, Technology\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJon started FoundOPS because of the great deal of potential he sees for the future for technology. He believes that the next revolution belongs to small business. “Everyday we see technology breaking down barriers and making more resources available.” FoundOPS hopes to help small businesses harness the incredible resources and opportunities that are now available to them.\r\n\r\nAt 21, Jonathan may be young, but he is no newcomer to the world of business software. During high school Jonathan got his start working as software consultant for the service industry. In college, he knew the potential that existed for a small business software platform and began working on a solution. The prototypes he developed have become the precursor to FoundOPS.\r\n\r\nWhen asked what he likes to do in his free time, Jonathan responds “Free time?” Despite his borderline obsessive commitment to FoundOPS, Jonathan still manages to sneak out of the office for the occasional bike ride or run. He’ll also read anything he can get his hands if he thinks it will give him a bit of knowledge. One day Jonathan hopes to have some time to travel the world and just meet people but for now he is happy right where he is.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nOren Shatken\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72288581\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/OrenShatken\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nCofounder and President, Product\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nThe son of an artist and an architect, Oren has always been torn between the worlds of form and function. At Purdue, Oren studied an eclectic mix of Political Science, Art and Design, Entrepreneurship, Viticulture, and Jewish Studies. Eventually he was approached by Jonathan with an interesting application of both form and function. “From what I’ve seen, business enterprise software suffers from an impressive lack of both. These issues are the result of years of decision-makers at large corporations with the luxury of not having to use the software they were purchasing.”\r\n\r\nNow Oren believes user interface has emerged as one of the most significant considerations for the future. “Technology has progressed to such an advanced stage that the bottleneck has become the connection between technology and the users. Computers now wait for us more than we wait for them.” By emphasizing simple and clean design practice, Oren hopes to create an interface that users will find intuitive and even addicting to use. “One day FoundOPS will be done when it does everything our users want and nothing else.”\r\n\r\nBeyond software, Oren loves spending time with his family and friends out on Shelter Island. An avid sailor, he claims his first crib was the v-berth (the triangle shaped bed located in the very front of a boat) on his father’s Cape Dory sailboat. When the snow falls outside the FoundOPS office, Oren dreams about skiing, but he’s concerned his techniques has suffered since he moved out to Indiana.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nZach Bright\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72290770\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/zbbright\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSenior Software Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nA die-hard Cubs fan, Zach hails from the suburbs of Chicago. At Purdue, Zach was a distinguished student of Computer Engineering, the president of his fraternity, all while working as a teaching assistant. Working with an entire fraternity of men or a class full of students taught Zach a great deal of patience. While Jon and Oren’s passion can create a great deal of excitement, we can always rely on Zach’s calming disposition to maintain order at FoundOPS.\r\n\r\nZach loves getting outside on a nice day and playing a few holes of golf. He’ll be happy where ever he is in the world as long he can tune in to watch the Cubs play.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nAndrew Pohl\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=70782535\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/apohl1111\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSilverlight Developer and Designer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nAndrew grew up in rural Indiana on a farm which might have something to do with his strong work ethic. “I leave work not when I’m tired, but when I’m done.” After earning his degree from Purdue in Computer Graphics Technology, Andrew joined the FoundOPS team as a Silverlight developer and has been invaluable for creating the look and feel of the site.\r\n\r\nWhen he’s not working on the project, Andrew enjoys spending time outdoors and playing Ultimate Frisbee. Occasionally he can be found kicking back and watching an action movie or two. His goals are modest but quickly becoming fulfilled; to be successful at something he enjoys.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nJohn Mahoney\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a style=\"margin-left:30px;\" href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=42714775\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSoftware Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJohn was originally from Virginia before moving out to California to study aerospace engineering. Before joining the FoundOPS team, John worked in IT for a number of years. Nowadays, John is known as the algorithms guys and has been responsible for developing much of the logic that makes FoundOPS dispatching so efficient.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time, John can be found working with his hands on various construction projects. He also enjoys producing music. One day John hopes to turn his talents towards space exploration.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','The Team','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-25','','','2011-09-23 13:16:41','2011-09-23 17:16:41','',21,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/21-revision-25/',0,'revision','',0),(81,1,'2011-09-23 13:17:20','2011-09-23 17:17:20','<div style=\"position: relative; top: -55px; left: 297px; background: none; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px;\">\r\n    <div id=\"navBoxTeam\">\r\n            <ul class=\"tabs\">\r\n                <li style=\"border-top:none;\"><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>\">Home</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">FoundOPS</a></li>    \r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">About Us</a>\r\n                    <ul class=\"subNav\">\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">The Team</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/values\">Our Values</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/jobs\">Jobs</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>/Home/ContactUs\">Contact Us</a></li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                </li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>\">Blog</a></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The Team</h1>\r\n<div class=\"titleBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"titleText\">We’re young, committed, and lean (in our development methodology, not necessarily our body types).</div>\r\n<div id=\"jonBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nJonathan Perl\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=40656805\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/jon_perl\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"jonBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nFounder and President, Technology\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJon started FoundOPS because of the great deal of potential he sees for the future for technology. He believes that the next revolution belongs to small business. “Everyday we see technology breaking down barriers and making more resources available.” FoundOPS hopes to help small businesses harness the incredible resources and opportunities that are now available to them.\r\n\r\nAt 21, Jonathan may be young, but he is no newcomer to the world of business software. During high school Jonathan got his start working as software consultant for the service industry. In college, he knew the potential that existed for a small business software platform and began working on a solution. The prototypes he developed have become the precursor to FoundOPS.\r\n\r\nWhen asked what he likes to do in his free time, Jonathan responds “Free time?” Despite his borderline obsessive commitment to FoundOPS, Jonathan still manages to sneak out of the office for the occasional bike ride or run. He’ll also read anything he can get his hands if he thinks it will give him a bit of knowledge. One day Jonathan hopes to have some time to travel the world and just meet people but for now he is happy right where he is.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nOren Shatken\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72288581\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/OrenShatken\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"orenBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nCofounder and President, Product\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nThe son of an artist and an architect, Oren has always been torn between the worlds of form and function. At Purdue, Oren studied an eclectic mix of Political Science, Art and Design, Entrepreneurship, Viticulture, and Jewish Studies. Eventually he was approached by Jonathan with an interesting application of both form and function. “From what I’ve seen, business enterprise software suffers from an impressive lack of both. These issues are the result of years of decision-makers at large corporations with the luxury of not having to use the software they were purchasing.”\r\n\r\nNow Oren believes user interface has emerged as one of the most significant considerations for the future. “Technology has progressed to such an advanced stage that the bottleneck has become the connection between technology and the users. Computers now wait for us more than we wait for them.” By emphasizing simple and clean design practice, Oren hopes to create an interface that users will find intuitive and even addicting to use. “One day FoundOPS will be done when it does everything our users want and nothing else.”\r\n\r\nBeyond software, Oren loves spending time with his family and friends out on Shelter Island. An avid sailor, he claims his first crib was the v-berth (the triangle shaped bed located in the very front of a boat) on his father’s Cape Dory sailboat. When the snow falls outside the FoundOPS office, Oren dreams about skiing, but he’s concerned his techniques has suffered since he moved out to Indiana.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nZach Bright\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=72290770\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/zbbright\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"zachBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSenior Software Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nA die-hard Cubs fan, Zach hails from the suburbs of Chicago. At Purdue, Zach was a distinguished student of Computer Engineering, the president of his fraternity, all while working as a teaching assistant. Working with an entire fraternity of men or a class full of students taught Zach a great deal of patience. While Jon and Oren’s passion can create a great deal of excitement, we can always rely on Zach’s calming disposition to maintain order at FoundOPS.\r\n\r\nZach loves getting outside on a nice day and playing a few holes of golf. He’ll be happy where ever he is in the world as long he can tune in to watch the Cubs play.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nAndrew Pohl\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=70782535\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div><div class=\"twitter\"><a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/apohl1111\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"andrewBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSilverlight Developer and Designer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nAndrew grew up in rural Indiana on a farm which might have something to do with his strong work ethic. “I leave work not when I’m tired, but when I’m done.” After earning his degree from Purdue in Computer Graphics Technology, Andrew joined the FoundOPS team as a Silverlight developer and has been invaluable for creating the look and feel of the site.\r\n\r\nWhen he’s not working on the project, Andrew enjoys spending time outdoors and playing Ultimate Frisbee. Occasionally he can be found kicking back and watching an action movie or two. His goals are modest but quickly becoming fulfilled; to be successful at something he enjoys.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBg\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnImg\" width=\"242px\" height=\"242px\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnDesc\">\r\n<div class=\"bigText\">\r\n\r\nJohn Mahoney\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"links\"><div class=\"linkedin\"><a style=\"position:relative; top:0px; left:30px;\" href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=42714775\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></div></div>\r\n<div id=\"johnBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"greyText\">\r\n\r\nSoftware Engineer\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nJohn was originally from Virginia before moving out to California to study aerospace engineering. Before joining the FoundOPS team, John worked in IT for a number of years. Nowadays, John is known as the algorithms guys and has been responsible for developing much of the logic that makes FoundOPS dispatching so efficient.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time, John can be found working with his hands on various construction projects. He also enjoys producing music. One day John hopes to turn his talents towards space exploration.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','The Team','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-26','','','2011-09-23 13:17:20','2011-09-23 17:17:20','',21,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/21-revision-26/',0,'revision','',0),(82,1,'2011-09-23 12:55:04','2011-09-23 16:55:04','<div id=\"beta\">\r\n<div id=\"navBoxBeta\">\r\n            <ul class=\"tabs\">\r\n                <li style=\"border-top:none; margin-top:2px;\"><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>\">Home</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">FoundOPS</a>\r\n			<ul class=\"subNav\">\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">Beta</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>/Home/Product\">Features</a></li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n		</li>    \r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">About Us</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>\">Blog</a></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n<h1 class=\"betaTitle\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Beta</h1>\r\n<div class=\"betaTitleBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"jobsTitleText\">\r\n<p>Experienced entrepreneurs say that you fall in love with a problem first, then you innovate a solution. At FoundOPS, the problems we’ve fallen in love with are those facing small field service companies. Where are my technicians? What job am I going to next? Have all of my customers paid me? If you’ve ever managed a service team, you know how difficult these problems can be. Wouldn’t it be great if there was a system that helped you keep track of everything? It would be easy to setup and easier to use. You would be able log in through your computer and see exactly where your team was. Assigning jobs would be as simple as dragging and dropping. Technicians would see their next jobs on their mobile phones and be able to use turn-by-turn navigation to get their fast. And it would be cloud based so your data would be secure and you could access it from anywhere with an Internet connection. </p>\r\n<p>Sounds simple enough, right? So that’s what we’ve set out to do. It’s taken some time, a few pivots, but now we’re starting to see a pretty good system take face. However in order for it to become a great system, we know we need your help. Did we make the buttons on our mobile app big enough for you to use with your work gloves on? Is there some feature you just have to have? If shaping the next generation of service software sounds like something you might be interested in, complete the form below and we’ll get in contact with you.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Beta','','inherit','open','open','','69-revision-6','','','2011-09-23 12:55:04','2011-09-23 16:55:04','',69,'http://localhost:55206/2011/09/23/69-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(83,1,'2011-09-23 13:23:39','2011-09-23 17:23:39','<div id=\"beta\">\r\n<div id=\"navBoxBeta\">\r\n            <ul class=\"tabs\">\r\n                <li style=\"border-top:none; margin-top:2px;\"><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>\">Home</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">FoundOPS</a>\r\n			<ul class=\"subNav\">\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/beta\">Beta</a></li>\r\n                        <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"foundopsLink\"];?>/Home/Product\">Features</a></li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n		</li>    \r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>/team\">About Us</a></li>\r\n                <li><a href=\"<?php echo $GLOBALS[\"blogLink\"];?>\">Blog</a></li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n<h1 class=\"betaTitle\" style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Beta</h1>\r\n<div class=\"betaTitleBar\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"jobsTitleText\">\r\n<p>Experienced entrepren